{"questionId":"5275560","questionHtml":"<p>Source S produces sound waves of speed <em>v</em> and frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>. S moves with constant velocity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math> away from a stationary observer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3d382f6e789f4d763c84b765a18e6bd11f6752db.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the frequency measured by the observer?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>f</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mi>f</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>f</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>f</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275560","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.29","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Source S produces sound waves of speed v and frequency f. S moves with constant velocity v5 away from a stationary observer. What is the frequency measured by the observer? A. 45f ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"29","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.5 – Doppler effect","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}